HEADWORD: Rustication
<hw>Rus`ti*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rusticatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of rusticating,
or the state of being rusticated; specifically, the punishment of a
student for some offense, by compelling him to leave the institution for
a time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Rustic work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

